_meanings:
{@--1@} To bow down, 
salute, make a low obeisance to, be 

humble (with <ab>acc.</ab> or dative); {#na#} 
{#praRamaMti devatAByaH#} <ls>K. 108</ls>; {#tAM#} 
{#BaktipravaRena cetasA praRanAma#} <ls>K. 228</ls>; <ls>Ku. 7. 27</ls>;
<ls>Bg. 11. 44</ls>; <ls>R. 2. 21.</ls> ({#sAzwAMgaM praRam#}
‘to fall down on the eight limbs’;
see {#azwAMga#}; {#daMqavat praRam#} ‘to bow by
throwing oneself down on the
ground quite prostrate and flat like
a stick placed horizontally, 
touching the ground at all points; <ab>cf.</ab>
{#daMqapraRAma#}).

To
cause to bow down; {#tAmarcitAByaH#} 
{#kuladevatAByaH kulapratizWAM praRamayya mAtA#}  
